# Auto Commit and Sync After Changes

Whenever you make code or config changes in this Cursor chat, you must **commit and sync** before considering the task complete. **Production closeout** (confirm deploy/CI, verify https://www.australianrates.com) is **mandatory** for every such chat unless waived—see **`every-chat-commit-deploy-verify-production.mdc`**.

1. **Branch (default)** – Before first commit for this task: sync `main`, then `git checkout -b agent/<slug>` (or `feat/…` / `fix/…`) per **`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`**, unless you are already on an appropriate feature branch or the user ordered direct `main`.
2. **After edits** – Once you have modified files in the repo:
   - Stage: `git add` (relevant paths or `.` as appropriate).
   - Commit: `git commit -m "brief description of change"`.
   - Push: `git push -u origin HEAD` (feature branch) or `git push origin main` **only** for an explicit hotfix on `main`.
3. **Pull request** – Open or update a **PR to `main`** (`gh pr create --base main` or UI); keep CI green; complete **`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`** **Bot feedback wait gate** (**not** immediate merge when CI passes); address **every** PR review bot thread **with replies** before merge or before enabling squash auto-merge.
4. **Scope** – Commit only the changes made in this conversation; use a message that describes what was done.
5. **No skip** – Do not leave the repo with uncommitted or unpushed changes unless the user explicitly asks you to stop before syncing.

If the user explicitly requests work **only** on `main`, follow that exception in **`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`**.
